==Contents==
''Meta-Trek'' is a ''[[Star Trek (1971 video game)|Star Trek]]'' style game where the object is to explore and claim as many of the 256 available quadrants as possible, while destroying enemy Binarians.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
J. Mishcon reviewed ''Meta-Trek'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 37.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Mishcon |first=J. |date=March 1981 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=37|pages=27}}</ref> Mishcon commented that "All in all, I would say that for those interested in a first rate original-Trek style game, this fits the bill nicely."<ref name="SG"/>

